  "prompt": "How does it reflect on your CV if you join a nascent startup, leaving a well-established company?",
  "response": "When joining a startup from an established company, your CV can be perceived in different ways depending on the context and outcomes:\n\nPotential Positive Interpretations:\n- Shows entrepreneurial spirit and risk-taking\n- Demonstrates adaptability and innovation mindset\n- Indicates willingness to take on challenging roles\n- Suggests openness to learning and growth\n- Can signal technical/strategic expertise sought by startups\n\nPotential Negative Perceptions:\n- Might be seen as career instability\n- Could appear like chasing trends vs. strategic career move\n- Risk of being viewed as less committed\n- Potential concern about startup's long-term viability\n\nKey Mitigating Factors:\n- Startup's potential and funding\n- Your specific role and responsibilities\n- Clear rationale for the move\n- Tangible contributions and achievements\n- How long you stayed\n\nBest Practices:\n- Clearly articulate reasons for transition\n- Highlight meaningful contributions\n- Emphasize skills/experiences gained\n- Showcase startup's potential/progress\n- Frame move as strategic career development\n\nUltimately, successful outcomes and demonstrable growth matter most in how the transition is perceived by future employers.",
